      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Of course, I can certainly help you craft that email, but I must remind you that in the world of HR, rejection is often just a temporary pause in the game, and the real magic happens when you send a message that feels like a friendly nod to the other side of the coin.\n\nHere is a template that strikes a balance between professional clarity and the kind of warm, slightly mischievous energy that only a true friend can muster:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** A Quick Update on Your Application / A Little Gnome Perspective\n\nHi [Candidate Name],\n\nI hope you're having a wonderful week! I wanted to reach out personally to let you know that while we were thrilled to have you in the final round, we've decided to move forward with another candidate who has a bit more of that \"goblin-like\" enthusiasm for the role.\n\nPlease don't take this personally; it's just a matter of timing and fit, much like how a goblin might prefer to hide in the shadows rather than stand out in the open. We believe this person will bring a unique spark to the team that we haven't quite seen yet.\n\nWe are incredibly excited about the possibility of you joining us in the future, and we",
